## Absorbed patterns (ideas/vocabulary only — no verbatim code or prose)

- `nidhinjs/prompt-master` (MIT) — prose-economy lens; see
  `skills/kerby/CLAUDE.md` § Authoring style.
- `addyosmani/agent-skills` (MIT) — two rules in
  `skills/kerby/resources/references/working-patterns.md` cite this repo as source.
- `elementalsouls/Claude-BugHunter` — discipline patterns in
  `skills/kerby/resources/references/validation.md`, `debugging.md`, and
  `working-patterns.md` (see file-level attribution).
- `DietrichGebert/ponytail` (MIT) — the ordered decision-ladder and the
  deliberate-shortcut upgrade-trigger ideas, in `resources/BOOTSTRAP.md` and
  `references/working-patterns.md` / `validation.md`.
- `shinpr/claude-code-workflows` (MIT) — two discipline rules in
  `references/validation.md` and `working-patterns.md`.
- `forrestchang/andrej-karpathy-skills` — the four-principle terseness compression
  check, in `references/working-patterns.md` § Scope Discipline.
- GSD (Get Shit Done) — five prose-level patterns across
  `references/sub-agent-delegation.md`, `implementation-planning.md`,
  `working-patterns.md`/`quality-gates.md`, `guardrails.md`, and `roadmap.md`.
- `paulDuvall/ai-development-patterns` (MIT) — the *Progressive Disclosure*
  pattern (a PreToolUse hook that matches the edited path against globs and
  injects a context pointer), reimplemented to kerby's hook convention as
  `skills/kerby/resources/hooks/route-high-stakes.sh`. Concept only — no
  verbatim shell.

The remaining entries in `resources/references/external-resources.md` are
cross-references (not absorbed) and carry their own inline links.
